	<p><b>Non-Tobacco User:</b> By choosing this option, you honorably verify 
	you do not currently use tobacco products, and you hereby pledge to not use 
	tobacco products through March 31, 2011.</p>
	<p>If you check the &quot;Not a Tobacco User&quot; option and ultimately use tobacco 
	products between April 1, 2010 and March 31, 2011, the following reporting 
	options are available:<br>
&nbsp;</p>
	<ol>
		<li>I will voluntarily notify St. Luke's Benefits Department immediately 
		at 208-381-1108.
		</li>
		<li>If it is later determined that I use tobacco products (through &quot;for 
		cause drug testing&quot;, as one example), notice of my failure to honor this 
		agreement will be immediately forwarded to St. Luke's Benefits 
		Department</li>
	</ol>
		<p>&nbsp;</p>
		<p>In both cases above, beginning the pay period following St. Luke's 
		Benefits Department notification, I understand I will be assessed a 
		separate, every-pay-period payroll deduction on an <u>after-tax basis</u>, 
		equal to the per-pay-period difference between the preferred premium 
		pricing and non-preferred premium pricing for my medical plan election.</li>
</form>
